SOUTH AFRICA: Study abroad to boost PhDs =96 proposal

Sharon Dell
An expert study has recommended that a large number of South African
students be sent abroad to study for doctoral degrees over the next 10
years, as one way to scale up the number of PhDs produced and boost the
country=92s knowledge and innovation system. The proposal is one of 10
contained in a report launched last week by the Academy of Sciences of
South Africa, Assaf.
Full report on the University World News site:
http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=3D20101015200903623

