STUDENT VIEW
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

UK: Muslim Veil: Why are we not accepting each other?

Burnley in Lancashire, England, is a city of simmering ethnic tension that
burst into violent riots between Muslims and non-Muslims in 2001. Yet
Burnley College has become the first in Britain to ban the veil or =91items
of clothing which cover the face=92 ostensibly for security reasons. Britain
has prided itself on being more tolerant than other European countries such
as France or Belgium that have banned the veil in schools, colleges or
public buildings. So what is it like to be a Muslim student from Burnley?
Find out from HUMA MOHYUDDIN.
Full report on the University World News site:
http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=3D20101015200529962
